===Etymology===
From A.D. 1250 in {{inh|en|enm|abbey}}, {{m|enm|abbeye||convent headed by an [[abbot]]}} (compare archaic English {{m|en|abbaye}}), itself borrowed from {{der|en|fro|abaie|abaïe}}, {{m|fro|abbaïe}}, {{m|fro|abeïe}}, {{m|fro|abbeie|abbeïe}} (Modern French {{m|fr|abbaye}}) from {{der|en|LL.|-}} or {{der|en|EL.|abbātia}}, from Classical Latin {{m|la|abbās||abbot}}. {{doublet|en|abbacy}}. See {{m|en|abbot}}.

[[Image:Fountains Abbey view crop1 2005-08-27.jpg|400px|thumb|Ruins of Fountains Abbey]]

